    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1897-05-03T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1897-05-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="99"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d99">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Sherman</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Denby</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1897-05-03">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 3, 1897</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 1437.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your No.
                    2713, of March 16 last, with further reference to your demand for the dismissal
                    of the delinquent magistrate, Liu Yao-kuang.</p>
                <p>The Department’s No. 1248, of the 28th ultimo, in reply to your No. 2705, of
                    March 11, instructs you to insist upon your demand. Great importance is attached
                    to this case.</p>
                <p>Respectfully, yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">John Sherman.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
